Professor Details

  • Ph.D.,University of Science and Technology, Republic of Korea.
  • M.S.,Inha University, Republic of Korea.
  • B.Sc. (Hons.),University of Dhaka, Bangladesh.

Reasearch

Major Fields of Specialization

  • Non-thermal Plasma sterilization, Food safety and hygiene, Food Microbiology, Food Chemistry, Biological chemistry, aerosol analysis, Analytical Chemistry, Asbestos analysis (Mg-silicate minerals, cause of mesothelioma, potential health risk for developing country).

    • Research Focus

  • Establishment of Single Particle Analytical (SPA) technique using SEM/EDX and ATR-FTIR and/or in combination: Rapid microbial detection, environmental aerosol analysis Microbial inactivation of pathogens both planktonic state and biofilm using atmospheric plasma Plasma decontamination of pesticides from fresh produce surface Plasma inactivation mechanism effect of individual radicals generated by plasma on microbes Evaluation of chemical (flavonoids, ascorbic acid extraction HPLC and LC-MS analysis), and physical quality of treated food sample.
